yed the land of the former Yugoslavia, but also left the deepest wounds in the memory of each of its belligerent nations. There are as many different interpretations of that bleak past as there are countries affected. It is therefore hard to expect absolute harmony when, less than two decades since the war ended, a diverse group of veterans gathers at a remote mountain hotel for a therapy session over several days. On the contrary, such a dangerously volatile situation can suddenly ignite by just one thoughtless word, or a seemingly dirty look. That’s because the former soldiers, obstinately holding on to their fundamental masculinity and their prejudices, refusing to expose the inhumanity of the atrocities perpetrated. However, this quietness is just about to be broken and hidden emotions are to be faced.","genre_ids":[18],"popularity":0.2222,"vote_count":11,"poster_path":"/n53Elz6bPG9AoYMtOYdUg843trl.jpg","release_date":"2017-10-05","vote_average":6.9,"backdrop_path":"/5ScZZ64LxyPOFIwGQ5D3PDPzD61.jpg","original_title":"Muškarci ne plaču","original_language":"bs"},{"id":1660,"adult":false,"title":"Small Change","video":false,"overview":"The lives of a motherless young man, who's just starting to find interest in women, and his physically abused, poverty stricken friend, are mixed with more or less innocent childhood experiences and challenges most their age experience.","genre_ids":[35,18],"popularity":0.5192,"vote_count":152,"poster_path":"/lBOkXZ2RsL2BO6NlrFgR9yT7J4I.jpg","release_date":"1976-03-17","vote_average":7.1,"backdrop_path":"/goBPr2y6uMU063J08bXuJjCAlil.jpg","original_title":"L'Argent de poche","original_language":"fr"},{"id":273096,"adult":false,"title":"My Man","video":false,"overview":"As a young child, Hana loses her family to a devastating tsunami that wipes out her town. At a shelter, distant relative Jungo sees her wandering and adopts her as his daughter.","genre_ids":[10749,80,18],"popularity":1.1025,"vote_count":27,"poster_path":"/74GsGG2geJF3